NEWSWIRE 
Pitcher Ron Darling and the New York Mets agreed on a 3-year, $5.3-million 
contract, and seven other players agreed to 1-year contracts, reducing the 
players in salary arbitration to 68. 
The seven are outfielder Bill Hatcher and pitchers Juan Agosto and Jim Deshaies 
of the Houston Astros; third baseman Jim Presley and catcher Dave Valle of the 
Seattle Mariners; catcher Joel Skinner of the New York Yankees, and pitcher 
Juan Nieves of the Milwaukee Brewers. 
Also, the Philadelphia Phillies signed free-agent left-hander Larry McWilliams 
to a 1-year contract plus an option for 1990. 
